Introduction

Jang Ye-eun, known under her stage name J, is a South Korean singer-songwriter and rapper under High Up Entertainment. She is best known as the Vocalist, Rapper and Maknae of the girl group STAYC.

Between 2017 and 2019 she was a trainee at JYP Entertainment. She then joined High Up Entertainment in 2019.

On October 14, 2020, J was revealed as the fifth member of STAYC. She officially debuted as a member of STAYC on November 12, 2020 with their first single album "Star To A Young Culture" with the title-track "So Bad".
